The process of combining chicken with one or more ingredients together.

Bird food is food (often varieties of seeds, nuts, or dried fruits) eaten by birds. The various types of bird food reflect the species of bird that can be fed, whether they are carnivores or nectar eating birds.
A nut butter made from soybeans that are roasted, crushed, and mixed with soybean oil to form a stiff textured food spread with a mild nutty flavor.
